The evidence with the title 'To what extent could planting trees help solve climate change ... ' says Nov 29, 2012  ... Outside of Kyoto , some tree-planting projects established to absorb CO2 have turned out to be nonviable due to the cost of acquiring inputs or protecting young trees from fire , drought , pests or diseases. The cost of land is another barrier to widespread tree - planting , especially where there iscompetition ... 
